{"action": "edit", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    teal_rectangles = []\n    rows, cols = input_grid.shape\n    flag = np.zeros([rows, cols])\n    for i in range(rows):\n        for j in range(cols):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == teal and (not flag[i, j]):\n                h, w = find_teal_rectangle(input_grid, i, j)\n                if h > 0 and w > 0:\n                    teal_rectangles.append((i, j, h, w))\n    max_red_rectangle = find_max_red_rectangle(teal_rectangles)\n    return max_red_rectangle\ndef find_max_red_rectangle(teal_rectangles: List[Tuple[int, int, int, int]], input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int, int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a list of teal rectangles and the input grid.\n    It finds the rectangle which has the most red pixels in it.\n    It returns a tuple of the starting coordinates (i, j) and the height and width of the rectangle.\n    \"\"\"\n    max_red_pixels = 0\n    max_red_rectangle = None\n    for i, j, h, w in teal_rectangles:\n        red_pixels = 0\n        for row in range(i, i + h):\n            for col in range(j, j + w):\n                if input_grid[row][col] == red:\n                    red_pixels += 1\n        if red_pixels > max_red_pixels:\n            max_red_pixels = red_pixels\n            max_red_rectangle = (i, j, h, w)\n    return max_red_rectangle\ndef find_teal_rectangle(input_grid: np.ndarray, i: int, j: int) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array representing a grid of pixels and the starting coordinates (i, j) of a teal pixel.\n    It then finds the height and width of the teal rectangle in the grid starting from the given coordinates (i, j).\n    The teal rectangle may contain blue and red pixels as well.\n    It returns a tuple of the height and width of the teal rectangle.\n    \"\"\"\n    rows, cols = input_grid.shape\n    height = 0\n    width = 0\n    for row in range(i, rows):\n        if input_grid[row][j] !